attributes.text:
@dev Returns the addresses of supported currencies for trading
 @return address[] An array of addresses of supported currencies

@dev Returns the address of the stable coin
 @return address The stable coin address

@dev Returns the addresses and names of supported oracle APIs
 @return OracleData[] An array of oracle API addresses and names

@dev Sets the address of the stable coin
 @param stableCoinAddress The address of the stable coin

addCurrencyKey(string,address).details: Adds a new tradable currency to the platform

params.currencyKey: The address of the currency to add
params.currencySymbol: The symbol of the currency to add

addOracleAPIAddress(string,address).details: Adds a new oracle API to the platform

params.name: The name of the oracle API
params.oracleAddress: The address of the oracle API

checkIfCurrencyIsAvailable(address).details: Given the address of a currency, returns whether the currency is supported on the platform

returns._0: bool Whether the currency is supported on the platform

getAvailableCurrencies().details: Returns the addresses of supported currencies for trading

returns._0: address[] An array of addresses of supported currencies

getCurrencyKeyFromIndex(uint256).details: Given the index in the array of available currencies, returns the currency key at that index

params.index: Index in the array of available currencies

returns._0: address Currency key at given index

getCurrencySymbol(address).details: Given the address of a currency, returns the currency's symbol

getOracleAPIName(address).details: Given the address of an oracle API, returns the name of the oracle API

params.oracleAddress: The address of the oracle API

getOracleAPIs().details: Returns the addresses and names of supported oracle APIs

returns._0: OracleData[] An array of oracle API addresses and names

getParameterValue(string).details: Given the name of a parameter, returns the value of the parameter

params.parameter: The name of the parameter to get value for

returns._0: uint The value of the given parameter

getStableCoinAddress().details: Returns the address of the stable coin

setParameterValue(string,uint256).details: Updates the address for the given contract; meant to be called by Settings contract owner

params.newValue: The new value of the given parameter
params.parameter: The name of the parameter to change

setStableCoinAddress(address).details: Sets the address of the stable coin

params.stableCoinAddress: The address of the stable coin

updateCurrencyKey(string,address).details: Updates the address of the given currency

params.newCurrencyKey: The new address for the given currency

updateOracleAPIAddress(address,address).details: Updates the address of a given oracle API

params.newOracleAddress: The new address of the given oracle API
params.oldOracleAddress: The address of the oracle API to update
